This paper proposes a graph convolutional network (GCN) framework for link prediction in knowledge graphs (KGs). The paper discusses the use of transformation assumptions on the relationship between the subject, the relation, and the object of a triple, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on modeling graph data, which is a topic in databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the task of link prediction, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
